sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>{registry-name}-https
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant RESTServer as REST Server<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant gRPCServer as gRPC Server<br/>9090/TCP gRPC
    participant Database as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over Client,Database: Flow 1: Authenticated Model Registry Query (via Route)

    Client->>Router: GET /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/models<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Router->>Route: HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    Route->>RBACProxy: HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Re-encrypted
    RBACProxy->>RBACProxy: Validate Bearer Token<br/>SubjectAccessReview
    RBACProxy->>RESTServer: HTTP/8080<br/>Authenticated (localhost)
    RESTServer->>Database: Query metadata<br/>TLS (optional)<br/>Password/Client Cert
    Database-->>RESTServer: Model metadata
    RESTServer-->>RBACProxy: JSON Response
    RBACProxy-->>Route: HTTPS Response
    Route-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Client,Database: Flow 2: Internal gRPC Call (ML Metadata)

    participant InternalClient as Internal Client Pod

    InternalClient->>gRPCServer: gRPC/9090<br/>ml_metadata.MetadataStoreService
    gRPCServer->>Database: Query artifacts<br/>TLS (optional)<br/>Password/Client Cert
    Database-->>gRPCServer: Artifact metadata
    gRPCServer-->>InternalClient: gRPC Response

    Note over Client,Database: Flow 3: Operator Reconciliation

    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as Controller Manager

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch ModelRegistry CRs<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: CR Created/Updated<br/>Watch Stream
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Resources<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>(Deployments, Services, Routes)
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Success Response

    Note over Client,Database: Flow 4: Webhook Validation

    participant User as User

    User->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ModelRegistry CR
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-modelregistry<br/>HTTPS/9443 TLS 1.2+<br/>TLS Client Cert
    Webhook->>Webhook: Validate CR Spec
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response<br/>(Allow/Deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created/Validation Error
